    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-04-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-04-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="11"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d11">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Hopkins Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Matthews</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d11fn1">The Department of State’s copy of this telegram is
                        filed under 841.24/1788.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-04-01">April 1,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2326. Embassy has received for transmission the following message from the Prime
                    Minister to Mr. Harry Hopkins: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <list>
                            <item>“1. Many thanks for yours of thirtieth.<note n="2" xml:id="d11fn2"
                                    >The message under reference has not been found, but it may be
                                    Hopkins’ telegram of March 29 to Churchill (Sherwood, p. 718) on
                                    the proposed award to MacArthur.</note> I look for good and
                                speedy results in Tunisia. I do trust you will give careful
                                consideration to my proposal for a meeting. There are so many things
                                that I want to talk over with you.</item>
                            <item>“2. I am much concerned at not hearing from you about <gloss
                                    target="#t_TubeAlloys1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tube Alloys</hi>
                                </gloss>. That we should work separately would be a sombre
                                    decision.”<note n="3" xml:id="d11fn3">For the earlier exchange
                                    of messages between Hopkins and Churchill on this subject, see
                                        <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1">pp.
                                        1</ref>–<ref target="#pg_6">6</ref>.</note>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Matthews</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
